{"embedding_dim": 1536, "data": [{"__id__": "chunk-acea47a4100c063ac37397f754d68522", "__created_at__": 1776302464, "content": "KENTUCKY RESIDENTIAL REAL ESTATE PURCHASE AND SALE AGREEMENT\nTransaction #: TC-2026-0042\nDate: March 15, 2026\n\n=======================================================================\nPARTIES\n=======================================================================\nSELLER: Robert and Linda Patterson\nAddress: 847 Maple Creek Drive, Louisville, KY 40218\nPhone: (502) 555-0133\nEmail: rpatterson@email.com\n\nBUYER: Carlos and Maria Hernandez\nAddress: 2231 Westport Road, Apt 4B, Louisville, KY 40212\nPhone: (502) 555-0287\nEmail: carlos.hernandez@gmail.com\n\nBUYER'S AGENT: Sarah Mitchell, License #RE-2019-4821\nBrokerage: Premier Real Estate Group\n\nSELLER'S AGENT: James Okafor, License #RE-2017-3305\nBrokerage: Bluegrass Premier Realty\n\nTRANSACTION COORDINATOR: ZHomes TC Platform\nTC Contact: tc@zhomesapp.com\n\n=======================================================================\nPROPERTY DESCRIPTION\n=======================================================================\nProperty Address: 1204 Sycamore Lane, Louisville, KY 40220\nLegal Description: Lot 14, Block 7, Sycamore Estates Subdivision,\n                   Jefferson County, Kentucky\nParcel ID: 050-28-14-007-00\nMLS #: 1687432\n\nProperty Type: Single-family residential\nYear Built: 1998\nSquare Footage: 2,340 sq ft\nBedrooms: 4\nBathrooms: 2.5\nGarage: 2-car attached\nLot Size: 0.28 acres\n\n=======================================================================\nPURCHASE PRICE & FINANCING\n=======================================================================\nPURCHASE PRICE: $385,000.00\nEARNEST MONEY DEPOSIT: $7,500.00\n  - Deposited with: Premier Real Estate Group Escrow Account\n  - Due by: March 19, 2026 (4 days after acceptance)\n\nFINANCING:\n  Loan Type: Conventional\n  Loan Amount: $308,000.00 (approximately 80% LTV)\n  Down Payment: $77,000.00 (20%)\n  Lender: First National Bank of Louisville\n  Loan Officer: Patricia Chen, NMLS #445821\n  \nFINANCING CONTINGENCY DEADLINE: April 12, 2026\n  Buyer must provide written financing commitment by this date.\n  If financing is not obtained, Buyer may cancel and receive full\n  earnest money refund.\n\n=======================================================================\nCLOSING & POSSESSION\n=======================================================================\nCLOSING DATE: April 30, 2026\nCLOSING ATTORNEY/TITLE COMPANY: Bluegrass Title & Escrow\n  Address: 333 West Vine St, Suite 200, Lexington, KY 40507\n  Contact: David Nguyen, Esq.\n  Phone: (859) 555-0922\n\nPOSSESSION: Seller to deliver possession at closing.\n  Any occupancy after closing subject to $150/day holdover fee.\n\n=======================================================================\nINSPECTION CONTINGENCIES\n=======================================================================\nHOME INSPECTION DEADLINE: March 25, 2026\n  Buyer has the right to conduct a general home inspection.\n  Inspector: Certified Home Inspectors of Kentucky\n  \nRADON INSPECTION DEADLINE: March 25, 2026\n\nTERMITE/WDO INSPECTION DEADLINE: March 28, 2026\n\nINSPECTION RESPONSE DEADLINE: March 28, 2026\n  Seller must respond to Buyer's repair requests within 3 days\n  of receiving Buyer's inspection report.\n\nREPAIR ALLOWANCE: Seller agrees to credit Buyer up to $5,000\n  at closing for repairs identified in the home inspection.\n  Items over $5,000 will be renegotiated.\n\n=======================================================================\nINCLUSIONS & EXCLUSIONS\n=======================================================================\nINCLUDED IN SALE:\n  - All kitchen appliances (refrigerator, dishwasher, range)\n  - Washer and dryer (Samsung units, 2022)\n  - All window treatments and blinds\n  - Attached light fixtures\n  - Garage door openers (2 remotes)\n  - Backyard shed\n  - Central HVAC system (installed 2020, under warranty until 2025)\n  - Water softener system\n\nEXCLUDED FROM SALE:\n  - Dining room chandelier (heirloom, will be replaced before closing)\n  - Backyard playset\n  - Basement freezer chest\n\n=======================================================================\nLEAD-BASED PAINT DISCLOSURE\n=======================================================================\nThis property was built in 1998, therefore no Lead-Based Paint\nDisclosure is required under 42 U.S.C. § 4852d.\n\n=======================================================================\nSELLER'S DISCLOSURE OF PROPERTY CONDITION\n=======================================================================\nPursuant to KRS Chapter 324.360, Seller discloses the following:\n\nSTRUCTURAL:\n  - Foundation: No known issues. Minor settling cracks in basement\n    wall repaired in 2021, cost $800.\n  - Roof: Replaced June 2022. 30-year architectural shingles.\n    GAF Materials warranty transferable to buyer.\n\nSYSTEMS:\n  - HVAC: Replaced 2020. Annual service performed December 2025.\n  - Water Heater: 50-gallon gas, installed 2019.\n  - Electrical: 200-amp service, updated 2015.\n  - Plumbing: No known issues.\n\nWATER INTRUSION: Basement had minor water seepage in 2019 during\n  100-year flood event. French drain system installed 2019.\n  No further incidents.\n\nENVIRONMENTAL: No known underground storage tanks, asbestos, \n  mold, or other environmental hazards.\n\nNEIGHBORHOOD: Property is not in a known flood zone.\n  FEMA Flood Zone: X (minimal flood hazard).\n\n=======================================================================\nCOMMISSIONS &", "full_doc_id": "doc-15e43a846209c4065c12f0a1b112478d", "file_path": "purchase_agreement_TC-2026-0042.txt", "vector": ""}, {"__id__": "chunk-0e2e80b56f12c0740ad861bb2e503188", "__created_at__": 1776302464, "content": "- Plumbing: No known issues.\n\nWATER INTRUSION: Basement had minor water seepage in 2019 during\n  100-year flood event. French drain system installed 2019.\n  No further incidents.\n\nENVIRONMENTAL: No known underground storage tanks, asbestos, \n  mold, or other environmental hazards.\n\nNEIGHBORHOOD: Property is not in a known flood zone.\n  FEMA Flood Zone: X (minimal flood hazard).\n\n=======================================================================\nCOMMISSIONS & FEES\n=======================================================================\nTOTAL COMMISSION: 5% of purchase price = $19,250.00\n  - Buyer's Agent Commission: 2.5% = $9,625.00\n  - Seller's Agent Commission: 2.5% = $9,625.00\n  - Paid by Seller at closing.\n\nTC FEE: $500.00 (paid by Seller to ZHomes TC Platform at closing)\n\nTITLE INSURANCE:\n  - Owner's Policy: Buyer's expense, estimated $850\n  - Lender's Policy: Buyer's expense, estimated $400\n\nESTIMATED CLOSING COSTS (BUYER):\n  - Loan origination fee: $2,310\n  - Appraisal: $550\n  - Title insurance: $1,250\n  - Recording fees: $95\n  - Prepaid items (insurance, taxes): ~$3,200\n  TOTAL ESTIMATED BUYER CLOSING COSTS: ~$7,405\n\nESTIMATED CLOSING COSTS (SELLER):\n  - Real estate commissions: $19,250\n  - TC Fee: $500\n  - Attorney fee: $600\n  - Deed preparation: $150\n  - Payoff of existing mortgage: $210,450 (approx)\n  TOTAL ESTIMATED SELLER PROCEEDS: ~$153,050\n\n=======================================================================\nCRITICAL DEADLINES CHECKLIST\n=======================================================================\n[ ] March 19, 2026 — Earnest money deposit due\n[ ] March 25, 2026 — Home inspection deadline\n[ ] March 25, 2026 — Radon inspection deadline\n[ ] March 28, 2026 — WDO/termite inspection deadline\n[ ] March 28, 2026 — Buyer's inspection response to Seller\n[ ] March 31, 2026 — Seller's repair response deadline\n[ ] April 5,  2026 — Appraisal ordered by lender\n[ ] April 12, 2026 — FINANCING CONTINGENCY DEADLINE (critical)\n[ ] April 15, 2026 — Homeowner's insurance binder due to lender\n[ ] April 20, 2026 — Final walkthrough scheduled\n[ ] April 28, 2026 — Closing disclosure provided (3 days before)\n[ ] April 30, 2026 — CLOSING DAY\n\n=======================================================================\nADDITIONAL TERMS\n=======================================================================\n1. APPRAISAL CONTINGENCY: If property appraises below $385,000,\n   Buyer may renegotiate, make up the difference, or cancel with\n   full earnest money refund.\n\n2. HOME SALE CONTINGENCY: None. Buyers have pre-qualified without\n   contingency on sale of current property.\n\n3. SURVEY: No survey required by lender. Existing survey on file\n   with Jefferson County Clerk acceptable.\n\n4. HOA: Property is NOT subject to a Homeowner's Association.\n\n5. UTILITIES: Seller to maintain all utilities through closing date.\n\n6. DISPUTE RESOLUTION: Any disputes shall be mediated through the\n   Greater Louisville Association of REALTORS® mediation program\n   prior to any legal action.\n\n7. GOVERNING LAW: This Agreement shall be governed by the laws\n   of the Commonwealth of Kentucky.\n\n=======================================================================\nSIGNATURES\n=======================================================================\nBUYER SIGNATURE: _____________________ Date: March 15, 2026\nCarlos Hernandez\n\nBUYER SIGNATURE: _____________________ Date: March 15, 2026\nMaria Hernandez\n\nSELLER SIGNATURE: _____________________ Date: March 16, 2026\nRobert Patterson\n\nSELLER SIGNATURE: _____________________ Date: March 16, 2026\nLinda Patterson\n\n=======================================================================\nTC NOTES (ZHomes Internal)\n=======================================================================\n- Transaction opened: March 16, 2026\n- File assigned to: TC Platform Auto\n- Priority: HIGH (closing April 30 - 45 day timeline)\n- Lender communication: Patricia Chen confirmed pre-approval March 14\n- Title company booked: Confirmed March 17\n- NOTE: Seller replacement chandelier must be documented before\n  closing walkthrough. Request photo confirmation from agent.\n- Roof warranty transfer: Request original documents from sellers.", "full_doc_id": "doc-15e43a846209c4065c12f0a1b112478d", "file_path": "purchase_agreement_TC-2026-0042.txt", "vector": ""}], "matrix": ""}